follow these steps to run the script:

within terminal, enter:  vim <filename>.sh
within vim, paste in the body text of UserPWRevisionTxtOutput
within vim, press esc key, then enter ":wq" to save file and exit vim editor
back in terminal, enter: chmod +x <filename>.sh
now run the file, in terminal enter "./<filename>.sh>

then to change root, enter "passwd root" followed by desired password.
all done!


